s, how our wastewater can be better managed, and to discover some of the best water solutions.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1575, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Video reports, an animated explainer series and live debate - find out why Water Matters, from Euronews.\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1673, \"end\": 1681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Euronews\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Climate Now  We give you the latest climate facts from the world's leading source, analyse the trends and explain how our planet is changing.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We meet the experts on the front line of climate change who explore new strategies to mitigate and adapt.\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 1931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Europe Today  The news and insights that drive Europe.\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1987, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"LIVE from Brussels, we deliver the top and exclusive stories shaping the EU and beyond, every morning.\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1998, \"end\": 2006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brussels\", \"score\": 0.9999998043263267, \"rank\": 1.9567377720147562e-07, \"text\": \"Brussels\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brussels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brussels\"}, {\"begin\": 2061, \"end\": 2063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.999999958265108, \"rank\": 4.169486669364281e-08, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay ahead with the key news and insights that matter in Europe today.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Ring  The Ring is Euronews' weekly political showdown, where Europe's toughest debates meet their boldest voices.\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In each episode, two political heavyweights from across the EU face off to propose a diversity of opinions and spark conversations around the most important issues of EU affairs and the wider European political life.\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2343, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.999999958265108, \"rank\": 4.169486669364281e-08, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2450, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.999999958265108, \"rank\": 4.169486669364281e-08, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No Comment  No agenda, no argument, no bias, No Comment.\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the story without commentary.\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My Wildest Prediction  Dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries  The Big Question  Deep dive conversations with business leaders  Euronews Tech Talks  Euronews Tech Talks goes beyond discussions to explore the impact of new technologies on our lives.\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With explanations, engaging Q&As, and lively conversations, the podcast provides valuable insights into the intersection of technology and society.\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Food Detectives  Europe's best food experts are joining forces to crack down on fraud.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Euronews is following them in this special series: The Food Detectives  Water Matters  Europe's water is under increasing pressure.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3160, \"end\": 3175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Detectives\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Food Detectives\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Detectives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Detectives\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pollution, droughts, floods are taking their toll on our drinking water, lakes, rivers and coastlines.\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join us on a journey around Europe to see why protecting ecosystems matters, how our wastewater can be better managed, and to discover some of the best water solutions.\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Video reports, an animated explainer series and live debate - find out why Water Matters, from Euronews.\", \"from\": 3511, \"to\": 3615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3606, \"end\": 3614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Euronews\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Climate Now  We give you the latest climate facts from the world's leading source, analyse the trends and explain how our planet is changing.\", \"from\": 3617, \"to\": 3758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We meet the experts on the front line of climate change who explore new strategies to mitigate and adapt.\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French conservatives and far-right figures have taken against the official poster for this summer's Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 3866, \"to\": 3981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3866, \"end\": 3872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9987417026309162, \"rank\": 0.0012598172137874765, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Failing to see thejoyful vibrancyof Ugo Gattoni's design, several political voices have fussed over the fact that a Christian cross and the French flag were missing on the images.\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 4162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4099, \"end\": 4114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_cross\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian cross\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_cross\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_cross\"}, {\"begin\": 4123, \"end\": 4134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those responsible for the image were \\\"ready to deny France, going so far as to distort reality to cancel its history\\\", Francois-Xavier Bellamy of the Republicans party wrote on X.\", \"from\": 4164, \"to\": 4343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4216, \"end\": 4222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.941716133673768, \"rank\": 0.061734972251580505, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4314, \"end\": 4325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"score\": 0.9999999927272256, \"rank\": 7.272672411364248e-09, \"text\": \"Republicans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Top of the list of complaints about the poster, whichdepicts a stylised panorama of Paris, is the absence of the cross that sits atop the Dome des Invalides, where Napoleon is buried.\", \"from\": 4345, \"to\": 4528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4429, \"end\": 4434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3813483241155323e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4509, \"end\": 4517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1980691416121778e-41, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What is the point of holding the Olympic Games in France if we then hide who we are?\\\"\", \"from\": 4530, \"to\": 4616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4581, \"end\": 4587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.941716133673768, \"rank\": 0.061734972251580505, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marion Marechal of the far-right Reconquete (Reconquest) party posted on X.\", \"from\": 4617, \"to\": 4692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, National Rally (RN) lawmaker Nicolas Meizonnet wrote that the omissions must be the result of \\\"wokism\\\".\", \"from\": 4694, \"to\": 4808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4705, \"end\": 4719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}, {\"begin\": 4734, \"end\": 4751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Meizonnet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Meizonnet\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Meizonnet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Meizonnet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This again...  For those of you hearing that reappropriated term bandied about all the time as the root cause of everything wrong with the modern world we live in, know that it did not use to be a bad thing.\", \"from\": 4810, \"to\": 5017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It still is not.\", \"from\": 5018, \"to\": 5034, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The term is derived from African-American Vernacular English, used in racial justice movements in the early to mid-1900s.\", \"from\": 5036, \"to\": 5157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5061, \"end\": 5096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African-American_Vernacular_English\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"African-American Vernacular English\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African-American_Vernacular_English\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African-American_Vernacular_English\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To be \\\"woke\\\" politically in the Black community means that someone is informed, educated and conscious of social injustice and racial inequality, as Merriam-Webster Dictionary defines.\", \"from\": 5158, \"to\": 5342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Essentially, a progressive outlook on a host of issues, specifically on race.\", \"from\": 5344, \"to\": 5421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The term began to gain more popularity at the start of the Black Lives Matter movement in 2014, and was used to wake people up to the social injustices of police brutality against the Black community following the fatal police shooting of Michael Brown.\", \"from\": 5423, \"to\": 5676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5662, \"end\": 5675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shooting_of_Michael_Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.264030158908368e-36, \"text\": \"Michael Brown\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shooting_of_Michael_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shooting_of_Michael_Brown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, hardly a bad thing.\", \"from\": 5678, \"to\": 5701, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The snag is that the word has since been co-opted by conversatives and right-leaners as a pejorative term to signify... well, anything they do not like the sound of.\", \"from\": 5703, \"to\": 5868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The word \\\"woke\\\" is now a catch-all term used to refer to either insincere or performative activism, or in phrases like \\\"woke ideology\\\" or \\\"the woke agenda\\\" - a dog whistle that allows those who use it to air their grievances about progressive values without deploying more extreme (usually racist) language.\", \"from\": 5870, \"to\": 6177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's frequently trotted out when talking about identity-based social justice issues; the questioning or denunciation of systemic injustices in society; racial education in schools; LGBTQ+ rights... Everything umbrellaed in so-called culture wars.\", \"from\": 6179, \"to\": 6425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And now, poster designs.\", \"from\": 6427, \"to\": 6451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gattoni's poster design features a cartoonish Paris cityscape with major landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower and a wealth of tiny details, including all 54 Olympic and Paralympic sports.\", \"from\": 6453, \"to\": 6638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6499, \"end\": 6504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3813483241155323e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6620, \"end\": 6637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In reaction to being pulled into France's culture wars, Gattoni said he had rendered buildings \\\"in the way they come to my mind, without any ulterior motive\\\".\", \"from\": 6640, \"to\": 6798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6673, \"end\": 6679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.941716133673768, \"rank\": 0.061734972251580505, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was never meant to be accurate - rather an Art Deco fantasy utopia of Paris.\", \"from\": 6800, \"to\": 6879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6846, \"end\": 6854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_Deco\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.791009594464641e-15, \"text\": \"Art Deco\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_Deco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_Deco\"}, {\"begin\": 6873, \"end\": 6878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3813483241155323e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 committee concurred, stating that the posters were a \\\"light-hearted interpretation of a reinvented stadium-city\\\".\", \"from\": 6881, \"to\": 7009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6885, \"end\": 6895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.223321830510591e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All this mini-scandal reveals is that once again, the bastardisation of a valuable term, now used as an insult, just makes outraged right-wingers look desperate.\", \"from\": 7011, \"to\": 7172, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The French conservatives fighting an imaginary culture war against a vibrant, Where's Wally-esque image designed to celebrate games that bring nations together is nothing but a ploy to get more votes and sow divisions.\", \"from\": 7173, \"to\": 7391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7177, \"end\": 7183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9987417026309162, \"rank\": 0.0012598172137874765, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What a bunch of Wallies.\", \"from\": 7393, \"to\": 7417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics are set to take place from 26 July - 11 August, followed by the Paralympics from 28 August - 8 September.\", \"from\": 7419, \"to\": 7543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Additional sources\\u2022 AFP      Browse today's tags\", \"from\": 7545, \"to\": 7593, \"entities\": []}]}"